From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: re-enable revision_check to generate gitinfo.h

The revision_check custom target was commented out, leaving gitinfo.h
never generated. gitinfo.cpp includes it unconditionally, so the build
fails with "gitinfo.h: No such file or directory".

Uncomment the target so cmake generates gitinfo.h at build time via
UpdateRevision.cmake, which gracefully falls back to hash "0000000"
when git is unavailable (e.g. in a Buildroot extracted source tree).
---
 src/CMakeLists.txt | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/CMakeLists.txt b/src/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/src/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -315,4 +315,4 @@
-#add_custom_target( revision_check ALL
-#	COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -P "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/tools/updaterevision/UpdateRevision.cmake" src/gitinfo.h
-#	WORKING_DIRECTORY ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}
-#)
+add_custom_target( revision_check ALL
+	COMMAND "${CMAKE_COMMAND}" -P "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/tools/updaterevision/UpdateRevision.cmake" src/gitinfo.h
+	WORKING_DIRECTORY ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}
+)
